metadata.name: Winter Solstice #14
metadata.description:
I watched as the sun began to rise, its rays spreading out across the sky, illuminating the landscape. I felt a sense of peace and contentment, and for a moment, all of my worries and troubles melted away. I was truly happy, and felt grateful to be alive and able to witness this beautiful moment.

As the sun climbed higher in the sky, I continued to watch, taking in the beauty of the winter solstice. I knew that this moment was fleeting, and that soon the days would start to get longer and the cold winter weather would give way to spring. But for now, I was content to just stand there and enjoy the moment.

The winter solstice was a reminder to me that there was always beauty and wonder to be found in the world, even in the darkest of times, as I stood there, watching the sun rise.

metadata.name: 365 DivideRect #2
metadata.description: 365 DivideRect is a stunning piece of generative art that uses the divideRect() function to create a complex and intricate pattern. With each iteration, the function divides a rectangle into two new triangles, resulting in a self-similar and recursive structure. The piece is rendered using a vibrant and varied color palette, adding an additional layer of visual interest and complexity to the pattern. :)

metadata.name: Chromoplasm #73
metadata.description:
Chromoplasms have 10 features which approximately describe their configuration, behavior and appearance. Like their predecessors monocells, they start from a basic primitive shape and develop in several stages through application of growth rules. Highest stage observed for a chromoplasm is 4, which is also GPU intensive to display and interact with. Each chromoplasm has both structural as well as behavioral features. Structural ones include starting primitive, stage (1-4) and order (symmetric / irregular), with many growth-related features remaining hidden. Behavioral features include reconfiguration of node connections, modulation of node distances and degeneration type. Occasionally, nodes change size in oscillating patterns. Around 300 color palettes are grouped in 8 categories.

Press o_o for recording an animation clip (available only in fullscreen / live mode). Press >< for recentering once, double click it to trigger automatic recentering. Coded in Javascript and GLSL using Three.js and D3 frameworks.

metadata.name: Unfolded #191
metadata.description:
A plane is repeatedly folded over itself, choosing creases either at random, or according to some pattern (like a grid). These creases form the boundaries of the individual textured tiles.

Once the folds are complete, they are undone in reverse order, recreating the original plane. With each unfolding, the orientation of each crease (as a mountain or a valley), and each tile (facing up or down) is recorded as a sequence of 1s and 0s. Tiles are colored and textured according to similarities in these binary sequences, giving rise to subtle symmetries and repetitions.

Written in vanilla JS & HTML5 Canvas.

metadata.name: Glomularus #194
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node
